>>>>>>> # Emotional and psychological support for people with diabetes (our
>>>>>>> ### The psychological and emotional wellbeing of people with diabetes
must be an integral part of diabetes care. We set out what needs to be done to
>>>>>>> Diabetes is a complex and demanding condition and effective management
is largely dependent on how people care for themselves. Consequently the
impact on emotional and psychological well-being can be profound.
>>>>>>> The mental wellbeing of people living with diabetes should be an
integral part of diabetes care. It is the responsibility of both commissioners
and care providers, and support should not be limited to people with
diagnosable psychological disorders. Clear leadership, practical action and
appropriate funding is required at both a national and local level.
